nel 76 (SD) <br/> Channel 124 (HD)\n| sat serv 10      = [[Dish TV Sri Lanka]]\n| sat chan 10      = Channel 2652 (SD)\n| sat serv 11      = [[realvu]]\n| sat chan 11      = Channel 310 (HD)\n| cable serv 1     = [[Fastway Cable]]\n| cable chan 1     = Channel 301 (SD) <br/>Channel 606 (HD)\n| cable serv 2     = [[In Digital]]\n| cable chan 2     = Channel 425\n| cable serv 3     = [[Asianet Digital TV]]\n| cable chan 3     = Channel 300 (SD) <br/>Channel 808 (HD) \n| cable serv 4    = [[Ask Cable Vision]] (Sri Lanka)\n| cable chan 4     = Channel 45\n| iptv serv 1      = [[PEO TV]]\n| iptv chan 1      = Channel 37 (SD)\n|iptv serv 2       = [[Net TV Nepal]]\n| iptv chan 2      = Channel 522 (SD) <br/>Channel 508 (HD)\n}}\n'''Sony SIX''' is an Indian [[pay television]] [[sports channel]] owned and operated by [[Sony Pictures Networks]], which also owns [[Sony Entertainment Television (India)|Sony Entertainment Television]] and [[SET Max]]. The channel is aimed at the [[Market segmentation#Demographic Segmentation|youth segment]].<ref name=etapr12>{{cite news|title=IPL 5: Multi Screen Media plans to air matches on SIX next year|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/features/et-realty/ipl-5-multi-screen-media-plans-to-air-matches-on-six-next-year/articleshow/12581740.cms|accessdate=9 April 2012|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|date=8 April 2012}}</ref> It was launched on 7 April 2012 and is the 14th sports channel in India. It also broadcasts original programmes like [[NBA Slam]].<ref name=thblmar12>{{cite news|title=Sony Six could be launching on a bouncy wicket |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/industry-and-economy/marketing/article3248004.ece?homepage=true&ref=wl_home |accessdate=6 April 2012 |newspaper=[[The Hindu Business Line]] |date=26 March 2012}}</ref>\n\nIt broadcasts [[association football|football]], [[cricket]], [[professional wrestling]], [[mixed martial arts]], [[rugby union]], [[basketball]] and [[badminton]].\n\nSony Six has the broadcasting rights for [[FIFA World Cup]],<ref>[http://www.livemint.com/Consumer/hPC1jchSvJxuqE6ttEVTfK/Sony-SIX-wins-broadcast-rights-for-FIFA-World-Cup-2014-and-2.html Sony SIX wins broadcast rights for FIFA World Cup 2014 and 2018]</ref>, [[Caribbean Premier League]], [[Copa Am\u00e9rica]], [[The FA Cup]], [[Italian Serie A]], [[La Liga]], [[The Rugby Championship]], [[Aviva Premiership]], [[Top 14]], [[Super Rugby]], [[National Football League]], [[National Basketball Association]], [[The Masters]], [[PGA Championship]], [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]], [[Premier Futsal]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Sony Pictures gets exclusive rights of Premier Futsal League|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sony-pictures-gets-exclusive-rights-of-premier-futsal-league/1/678917.html|website=[[India Today]]|publisher=India Today|accessdate=1 July 2016}}</ref> and [[Total Nonstop Action Wrestling|Impact Wrestling]]<ref name=bsaug13>{{cite news|title= Sony Six acquires TNA Wrestling's broadcasting rights|url= http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/sony-six-acquires-tna-wrestling-s-broadcasting-rights-113080100698_1.html|accessdate=1 August 2013|newspaper=[[Business Standard]]}}</ref>\n\n[[Sony Pictures Networks India|Sony]] and its sister channel have broadcasting rights of the following international cricketing boards<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/22132423/wicb-signs-seven-year-tv-rights-deal |title=West Indies Cricket Board production and International broadcast rights from 2012-2019 contract |work=www.espncricinfo.com}}</ref> and franchise league:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Event !!Period\n|-\n! colspan=2|International\n|-\n|[[Cricket in Australia|International Cricket in Australia]]<ref name=\"Aus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cricket.com.au/news/sony-acquire-television-broadcast-rights-australian-cricket-india-subcontinent-ashes-star/2017-10-10||title= CA announce new Indian TV rights deal|website=Cricket Australia|date=10 October 2017|accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref>\n|2017-2023\n|-\n|[[Cricket in England|International Cricket in England]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Consumer/m5fbgvL7fDcREgKnUGo00K/Sony-Pictures-acquires-media-rights-for-cricket-matches-in-E.html|title=Sony Pictures acquires media rights for cricket matches in England|website=LiveMint|date=5 March 2018|accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref>\n|2018-2023\n|-\n|[[Cricket in South Africa|International Cricket in South Africa]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/taj-television-acquires-tv-rights-for-csa/844289/|title=Taj Television acquires TV rights for CSA|website=Indian Express|date=10 September 2011|accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref>\n|2012-2020\n|-\n|[[Cricket in Pakistan|International Cricket in Pakistan]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/sports/pakistan-cricket-board-renews-deal-with-ten-sports-for-next-five-years-150401|title=Pakistan Cricket Board renews deal with Ten Sports for next five years|website=Indian Television|date=1 April 2015|accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref>\n|2015-2020\n|-\n|[[Cricket in Sri Lanka|International Cricket in Sri Lanka]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/cricket/slc-broadcast-and-production-rights-go-to-ten-sports|title=Sri Lanka Cricket broadcast and production rights go to Ten Sports|website=Sports Keeda|date=10 July 2013|accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref>\n|2013-2020\n|-\n! colspan=2|Franchise League\n|-\n|[[Big Bash League]]<ref name=\"Aus\"/>\n|2017-2023\n|-\n|[[Caribbean Premier League]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insidesport.co/sony-retains-broadcasting-rights-for-caribbean-premier-league/|title=SONY retains broadcasting rights for Caribbean Premier League|website=Inside Sports India|date=7 June 2017|accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref>\n|2014-2017\n|} No customer service number why watching your channels\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Sports Television in India}}\n{{Sony Pictures}}\n{{Sony Corp}}\n\n[[Category:Sports 